    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="bibliography" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/> <citedRange>36B</citedRange></bibl>
                  (<bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2013"/>, <citedRange>§ 206</citedRange></bibl>;
                  <bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2017"/>, <citedRange>59</citedRange></bibl>;
                  <bibl><ptr target="#Bonnechere2018"/>, <citedRange>§ 33 n. 106</citedRange></bibl>;
                  <bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2018"/>, <citedRange>333 and 338 no. 17</citedRange></bibl>).
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="B">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><rs type="deity" ref="#theos"><w lemma="θεός">θεὸς</w></rs> <rs type="deity" ref="#tyche"><w lemma="τύχα">τύχα</w></rs> <w lemma="ἀγαθά">ἀγαθά·</w> <persName><name nymRef="#Φιλοτίδος"><unclear>Φ</unclear>ιλοτίδος</name></persName> τὰ <w lemma="σιδάρια">σιδά
                        <lb n="2" break="no"/>ρια</w> δικαίο̅ς;        
                </ab>
                </div>
          </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>God. Good Fortune. Do the iron objects rightfully belong to Philotis?</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>This private enquiry, which does not include the name of the consultant, belongs to the well-attested category of consultations concerning <rs type="theme" ref="#property">property matters</rs>, in this case the rightful ownership of <foreign xml:lang="grc">σιδάρια</foreign> by a woman named <persName><name nymRef="#Φιλοτίδος">Philotis</name></persName>; on legal disputes in the Dodona oracular tablets, see <bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2018"/></bibl>. According to <bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2017"/>, 59</bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">σιδάρια</foreign> refers to iron objects and not to the Byzantine coinage <foreign xml:lang="grc">σιδάρεοι</foreign>, as proposed by the editors of <bibl><ptr target="#DVC"/>I. Dodone DVC</bibl>.</p>
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#Chaniotis2018"/>, 338, no. 17</bibl>) interprets the text as an oracular response. On the controversial issue of the presence of answers on the Dodona tablets, see <bibl><ptr target="#MartínGonzález2021"/></bibl>.</p>
                <p><emph>Ithaca's results</emph>: <ref target="https://dodonaonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/IDodone_Online_36_Ithaca.html">Results</ref>, <ref target="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IDodone/IDodoneOnline/refs/heads/main/ithaca-results/IDodone_Online_36.md">Metadata</ref></p>
        </div>
        </body>
